quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,18,"Whoever has been wanting the hasty<i class=""s"">(life of this world) </i>—We hasten for him therein whatever We will to whomever We desire. Then We assigned{1}for him Hell where he roasts, condemned, defeated.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  17,19,"But whoever wanted the Hereafter and, as a believer, pursued it as it should be pursued, those—their pursuit has always been thanked."
  17,20,"To all—these and these<i class=""s"">(as well) </i>—We extend from the gifts of your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord<a class=""sup""><sup>b </sup></a>, for the gifts of your Lord have never been restricted."
  17,21,"Look<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>at how We have favored some of them over others, yet the Hereafter is more superior in degrees<i class=""s"">(of rank) </i>and more superior in preference."
  17,22,"Do<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not set up another god with Allah, lest you remain condemned,damned."
  17,23,"And your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord has decreed that you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>shall worship none but Him, and<i class=""s"">(He has decreed) </i>excelling in doing good to both parents. If either of them or both of them reach old age with you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, then do not say to them “Fie” nor scold them, but speak to them using noble words."
  17,24,"And lower to them the wing{1}of humility, out of mercy, and say, “My Lord, have mercy on both of them as they raised me when I was a child.”",footnotes:1:An expression that implies showing compassion.
  17,25,"Your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord knows better what is within yourselves. If you are righteous—indeed, He has always been Oft-Forgiving to the ones who often turn<i class=""s"">(to Him) </i>."
  17,26,"And give<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>the relative his rights, and the destitute<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and the traveler in need, and do not squander wastefully."
  17,27,"Indeed, the squanderers have always been brethren of the Satans, for Satan has always been a staunch denier of his Lord."
